<subSubSection id="C3776556EFA73ACDFC9AFA77FBE5F813" lastPageId="248" lastPageNumber="249" pageId="246" pageNumber="247" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEFA73AC3FC9AFA77FABFF8AD" blockId="246.[810,1452,1363,2070]" pageId="246" pageNumber="247">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEFA73AC3FC9AFA77FB4BFA12" bold="true" box="[863,1166,1465,1491]" pageId="246" pageNumber="247">Description of female</emphasis>
. Body (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EFA73AC3FADDFA77FA61FA15" box="[1304,1444,1465,1492]" captionStart="FIGURE 165" captionStartId="247.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[234,1358,215,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-18@247.[192,1396,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="247" captionText="FIGURE 165. Bonnierilla similis Illg &amp; Dudley, 1961, female. A, habitus, right; B, caudal ramus; C, rostrum; D, antenna; E, distal part of antenna; F, mandible; G, paragnath; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped; K, leg 1. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, D, F, H-K, 0.05 mm; C, 0.1 mm; E, G, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591596/files/figure.png" pageId="246" pageNumber="247">Fig. 165A</figureCitation>
) compressed, 2.58 mm long. Cephalosome produced into blunt projections at posterolateral corners of dorsal shield. Metasome consisting of well-defined first to fourth pedigerous somites in unexpanded specimen; greatest dorsoventral depth of metasome 0.55 mm. Free urosome 5-segmented: 4 abdominal somites becoming gradually shorter and narrower posteriorly. Caudal ramus (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EFA73AC3FCF7F907FC60F925" box="[818,933,1737,1764]" captionStart="FIGURE 165" captionStartId="247.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[234,1358,215,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-18@247.[192,1396,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="247" captionText="FIGURE 165. Bonnierilla similis Illg &amp; Dudley, 1961, female. A, habitus, right; B, caudal ramus; C, rostrum; D, antenna; E, distal part of antenna; F, mandible; G, paragnath; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped; K, leg 1. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, D, F, H-K, 0.05 mm; C, 0.1 mm; E, G, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591596/files/figure.png" pageId="246" pageNumber="247">Fig. 165B</figureCitation>
) elongate, slightlycurvedventrally, gradually narrowing distally and 4.8 times longerthan wide (226×47 μm); armed with 6 naked setae, outer lateral and dorsal setae located at 37 and 58% of ramus length, respectively; longest distal seta about 0.35 times as long as ramus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEFA73ACDFC9AF8BAFE10FA51" blockId="246.[810,1452,1363,2070]" lastBlockId="248.[136,778,1295,2070]" lastPageId="248" lastPageNumber="249" pageId="246" pageNumber="247">
Rostrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EFA73AC3FC12F8BAFB95F84F" box="[983,1104,1907,1934]" captionStart="FIGURE 165" captionStartId="247.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[234,1358,215,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-18@247.[192,1396,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="247" captionText="FIGURE 165. Bonnierilla similis Illg &amp; Dudley, 1961, female. A, habitus, right; B, caudal ramus; C, rostrum; D, antenna; E, distal part of antenna; F, mandible; G, paragnath; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped; K, leg 1. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, D, F, H-K, 0.05 mm; C, 0.1 mm; E, G, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591596/files/figure.png" pageId="246" pageNumber="247">Fig. 165C</figureCitation>
) longerthanwide, tapering. Antennule 8-segmented; first and second segments much broader than distal 6 segments; setation not elucidated due to damage to specimens. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EFA73AC3FAC0F814FABBF835" box="[1285,1406,2009,2036]" captionStart="FIGURE 165" captionStartId="247.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[234,1358,215,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-18@247.[192,1396,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="247" captionText="FIGURE 165. Bonnierilla similis Illg &amp; Dudley, 1961, female. A, habitus, right; B, caudal ramus; C, rostrum; D, antenna; E, distal part of antenna; F, mandible; G, paragnath; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped; K, leg 1. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, D, F, H-K, 0.05 mm; C, 0.1 mm; E, G, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591596/files/figure.png" pageId="246" pageNumber="247">Fig. 165D</figureCitation>
) 4- segmented; last segment (compound distal endopodal segment) forming broad, rounded subdistal tubercle armed with 3 setae, distal margin with 5 setae, 3 equal in length, broad, rod-shaped, and fused at base (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EFA93ACDFD4DFA9DFD39FAAF" box="[648,764,1363,1390]" captionStart="FIGURE 165" captionStartId="247.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[234,1358,215,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-18@247.[192,1396,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="247" captionText="FIGURE 165. Bonnierilla similis Illg &amp; Dudley, 1961, female. A, habitus, right; B, caudal ramus; C, rostrum; D, antenna; E, distal part of antenna; F, mandible; G, paragnath; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped; K, leg 1. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, D, F, H-K, 0.05 mm; C, 0.1 mm; E, G, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591596/files/figure.png" pageId="248" pageNumber="249">Fig. 165E</figureCitation>
); terminal claw short and stout.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF126655EFA63AC2FF4DF8BDFC49F813" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591596" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4591596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591596/files/figure.png" pageId="247" pageNumber="248" startId="247.[136,245,1907,1933]" targetBox="[234,1358,215,1844]" targetPageId="247">
