</caption>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEFA93ACDFF78FA59FDB9F84F" blockId="248.[136,778,1295,2070]" pageId="248" pageNumber="249">
Labrum not examined. Mandible (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EFA93ACDFDFEFA59FD6FFA73" box="[571,682,1431,1458]" captionStart="FIGURE 165" captionStartId="247.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[234,1358,215,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-18@247.[192,1396,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="247" captionText="FIGURE 165. Bonnierilla similis Illg &amp; Dudley, 1961, female. A, habitus, right; B, caudal ramus; C, rostrum; D, antenna; E, distal part of antenna; F, mandible; G, paragnath; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped; K, leg 1. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, D, F, H-K, 0.05 mm; C, 0.1 mm; E, G, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591596/files/figure.png" pageId="248" pageNumber="249">Fig. 165F</figureCitation>
) 5 teeth, 1 subsidiary tooth between distal first and second teeth; basiswith 1 medial seta; exopod with3 longproximal setae and 2 unequal, shorter setae distally; endopod obscurely articulated with basis, armedwith 4 and 9 setaeon first and second segments, respectively. Paragnath (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EFA93ACDFD4AF98FFCC4F99D" box="[655,769,1601,1628]" captionStart="FIGURE 165" captionStartId="247.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[234,1358,215,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-18@247.[192,1396,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="247" captionText="FIGURE 165. Bonnierilla similis Illg &amp; Dudley, 1961, female. A, habitus, right; B, caudal ramus; C, rostrum; D, antenna; E, distal part of antenna; F, mandible; G, paragnath; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped; K, leg 1. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, D, F, H-K, 0.05 mm; C, 0.1 mm; E, G, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591596/files/figure.png" pageId="248" pageNumber="249">Fig. 165G</figureCitation>
) with large, claw-like apical process. Maxillule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EFA93ACDFD55F9ADFCC7F9BF" box="[656,770,1635,1662]" captionStart="FIGURE 165" captionStartId="247.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[234,1358,215,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-18@247.[192,1396,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="247" captionText="FIGURE 165. Bonnierilla similis Illg &amp; Dudley, 1961, female. A, habitus, right; B, caudal ramus; C, rostrum; D, antenna; E, distal part of antenna; F, mandible; G, paragnath; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped; K, leg 1. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, D, F, H-K, 0.05 mm; C, 0.1 mm; E, G, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591596/files/figure.png" pageId="248" pageNumber="249">Fig. 165H</figureCitation>
) as usual for genus, but arthrite bearing 10 setae; seta on coxal endite broad; proximal seta on basis much shorter than distal 2. Maxilla (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EFA93ACDFE4DF907FE37F925" box="[392,498,1737,1764]" captionStart="FIGURE 165" captionStartId="247.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[234,1358,215,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-18@247.[192,1396,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="247" captionText="FIGURE 165. Bonnierilla similis Illg &amp; Dudley, 1961, female. A, habitus, right; B, caudal ramus; C, rostrum; D, antenna; E, distal part of antenna; F, mandible; G, paragnath; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped; K, leg 1. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, D, F, H-K, 0.05 mm; C, 0.1 mm; E, G, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591596/files/figure.png" pageId="248" pageNumber="249">Fig. 165I</figureCitation>
) also as usual for genus; 9 setae on syncoxa arranged as 3, 1, 2, and 3; claw on basis finely spinulose along both margins; 3 endopodal segments with 1, 1, and 3 setae, respectively. Maxilliped (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EFA93ACDFF55F89CFF3AF8AD" box="[144,255,1873,1900]" captionStart="FIGURE 165" captionStartId="247.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[234,1358,215,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-18@247.[192,1396,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="247" captionText="FIGURE 165. Bonnierilla similis Illg &amp; Dudley, 1961, female. A, habitus, right; B, caudal ramus; C, rostrum; D, antenna; E, distal part of antenna; F, mandible; G, paragnath; H, maxillule; I, maxilla; J, maxilliped; K, leg 1. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, D, F, H-K, 0.05 mm; C, 0.1 mm; E, G, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591596/files/figure.png" pageId="248" pageNumber="249">Fig. 165J</figureCitation>
) incompletely 2-segmentedwith 10 setaeon first segment and 2 unequal setae on second.
</paragraph>
